Description: fix out-of-bounds write in FFI VLA buffers (GC64 segfault)
 All uses of glIntv(0) (and equivalent) create zero-element VLA cdata arrays.
 GL functions such as glGetShaderiv, glGenBuffers, glGenVertexArrays then write
 one integer into array[0], which is past the end of the allocation.
 .
 On system LuaJIT (GC64 mode), the GC object header is 8 bytes larger than in
 non-GC64 mode. The out-of-bounds write lands on the nextgc pointer of the
 adjacent GC object, corrupting the GC chain. This causes an "Invalid write of
 size 8" in Valgrind and a segfault during the next incremental GC step.
 .
 Fix: change glIntv(0) to glIntv(1) (and equivalents) in all 12 affected files
 so that each "output pointer" buffer has room for the one value GL writes.
